# AI Agent Rules for Quizzer Project

## Code Quality Requirements

BEFORE committing ANY code changes, you MUST run these checks:

### Backend (Python/Django in /service)
1. Format: `cd service && black --check --line-length=100 .`
2. Lint: `cd service && flake8 . --max-line-length=100 --extend-ignore=E203,W503`
3. Test: `cd service && python manage.py test`

### Frontend (TypeScript/Svelte in /app)
1. Lint: `cd app && bun run lint`
2. Type check: `cd app && bun run check`
3. Test: `cd app && bun run test`
4. Build: `cd app && bun run build`

## Why These Checks Are Required

- GitHub Actions CI/CD runs these same checks
- Failing to run them locally will cause CI failures
- These ensure code quality and prevent regressions

## Testing Philosophy

See app/TESTING.md for testing guidelines:
- Focus on high-value tests for complex logic
- Avoid trivial tests for simple setters/getters
- Test behavior, not implementation

